non-examples, i.e. spaces that are not manifolds. The main
motivation for this post is to dispel some false notions about
manifoldsâ€”the term has been so common in certain circles that it is
almost synonymous with â€˜data.â€™ However, as I tried to explain in my
previous post, a manifold is a space that is exceptionally
well-behaved and, most importantly, homogeneous.1 To reiterate my favourite
definition:2 a d-dimensional manifold M is a space that
